1. Overview

This document contains details regarding how to navigate the WLU GO web application created by our team. The application is deployed on heroku at https://wlugoapp.herokuapp.com/.

 In this overview we would like to capture a few key things:

  1. Sign Up/Log In is a requirement - The data displayed on our front end is obtained from an API we created that links to our database. 

The base API URL is https://wlugo-app.herokuapp.com/api/ and requires token authentication to access thus resulting in the need for users to sign up and sign in for requests to run successfully.

As part of our submission we have included the documentation that outlines the various endpoints that we have for the API.

  1. Data Used  -
    1. Course Data - Our goal was to relate the application to Laurier, as part of this effort the data we used for the course selection page was obtained by web scraping the Loris Course Page and the Laurier VSB. 

We obtained 1500+ courses offered at Laurier and after data cleaning and transformation we were left with 425 entries that we added to the database. 

    1. Review Data-  In order to give the application a robust feel, we used actual reviews for the review content as opposed to using Lorem Ipsum. 

The data we used for this was obtained from Kaggle and relate to reviews of Cousera courses. Each course that we have has at least 8 - 12review entries giving us a total of 4000+ reviews. 

Since the review data was obtained from an external source in some cases the review may not relate the course that it was created for and may at times mention the actual Cousera course it was created about.

For these reviews to be populated we created 120 virtual users and assigned the coursera reviews we entered to a particular user. 

  1.  Incase of Failed Login or need to view a user with previous review data - In case of any potential issues during sign up when marking, kindly use the details below to log in.

Username

2. Homepage


The website url navigates users to the homepage. The home page contains details about what the application does and has a “Sign In or Sign Up” button that redirects to the sign-in page. 

The navigation bar at the top of the site is shared across all pages. 

Clicking on the “wlugo” logo at the top right returns users to the homepage.

3. Navigation Bar

4. User Authentication

User Sign-In 


This is the first step to using the application. The sign in options on the homepage are located on the top navigation bar as “Sign In”. Alternatively a user can click the blue “Sign In or Sign Up” button. 

When clicked, either one of the options above will redirect to the sign in page below. 


Sign-In Errors

Assuming the correct details were entered then the site will redirect the user to the course page. If the details were wrong then the following error shows up: 


The above error indicates that the details entered do not correspond to a user specific user account. The solution involves ensuring that the details entered are the same as those used to sign up. 

Sign Up 


The sign-up option is located on the navigation bar as shown in the image above. Clicking “Sign Up” redirects the users to the page below. 


The requirements for the field are shown below:

Field

Requirements

Username

Has to be more than 3 letters long 

Has to be unique 

Email

Has to follow standard email format

Has to be unique 

Password

Has to be 8 or more characters long 

Confirm Password

Has to be the same as the initial password entered 

 

If the details entered were correct, the user details will be added to the database and the users will be redirected to the sign-in page detailed earlier on. 

Sign-Up Errors 

The sign-up errors may result from the requirements above not being met. The errors will be flagged as shown below: 



To remedy the sign up issues, make sure that the details entered meet the criteria defined above. 

5. Course Selection

Once a user has signed in they are redirected to the course selection page. The user name is added to the navigation bar. In this case I will sign In as user Addie.


If the courses API endpoint ran successfully, then above the search bar an info panel will appear the words “Welcome, Course Data Is Available”.

Also note that in the navigation bar, the sign in and sign up option are not available anymore. If the current user logs out then these options will appear. 

Click the select dropdown bar and all possible options will be displayed as shown below.


Scroll through the list and select a course that you would like to see reviews about. In our case we will select “EC 640 - Macroeconomics 1” 


Click “Proceed”, this will redirect us to the course review page for the course that we just selected. 

6. Review


As you can see this page is divided into two main parts. The main banner portion at the top contains the details regarding the course as well as the average review information. 

Main Course Banner Portion


As noted in our other documentation the details above represent 

Banner Item 

Meaning 

Course Code 

The 2 letter and 3 digit code of a course 

Course Name

The name of a course offered at Laurier.

Department 

The department to which a particular course offered belongs. 

Number of reviews 

The number of reviews that have been made with respect to that course.

Birdness 

The average of how easy the course was for all users as a percentage.

Usefulness

The average of how useful reviewers thought the course was as a percentage.

Enjoyability

The average of how enjoyable the reviewers thought the course was  as a percentage. 

Add your review 

Button that redirects users to the review creation page 

 

Ratings and Review Course Banner Portion


This part captures each review that was made and the details included. The birdness, enjoyability and usability have a maximum rating of 5 and they are represented using stars. Additionally, we show the grade obtained, username and the review that they made of the course. 

7. Create Review

To create a review we need to click the “Create Your Review” Button at the base of the main banner. 


The create review page is made up of a partially pre-filled form that we need to complete to create a review. 

The required field and conditions are: 

Field 

Conditions 

Username 

Pre-filled and cannot be edited 

Course Id 

Pre-filled and cannot be edited

Rating Id 

Pre-filled and cannot be edited 

Birdness 

Has to be a number 

Minimum value is 1

Maximum value is 5 

Usefulness 

Has to be a number 

Minimum value is 1

Maximum value is 5 

Enjoyability

Has to be a number 

Minimum value is 1

Maximum value is 5 

Grade

The alphabet grade received for the course. Examples are provided

Term taken 

Has to have semester details. 

Examples are provided.

Review 

Maximum of 700 words.

 

Once the details are filled in, click “Submit Review”. If the entered information meets the above criteria then the user will be redirected to the course selection page. Select the course you made a review and you will notice that your review has been added. 

8. User Details

To view the user details, click the button on the navigation bar that contains the username. 


Clicking the button will redirect users to the user details page. 


The page contains 3 buttons: 

The first one simply details the username. 

The third button offers the log out option and redirects users to the homepage. An alternative way to sign out is using the Log Out Item on the nav bar. Clicking this redirects the user to the homepage and the navigation bar repopulates with the sign-in and sign-up option.  

The third button “My Reviews” redirects to a page that displays in a tabular format the reviews that the user has made before. Since we are logged in as “Addie” below is a snippet of a few entries made by Addie. 


To see the review made, click on the row and the actual review will drop down as shown below.
